Template: `v-if="showSplitItemModal"`, `fixed inset-0 z-[10000] ... bg-black/50 backdrop-blur-xs`, white `rounded-2xl max-w-lg`. Lists source table's items (`restaurantStore.tableOrders[selectedTableForAction?.code]?.items`), checkboxes (`selectedItemsToSplit`), per-item qty stepper (`splitItemQuantities`, `changeSplitQty`), summary (`splitItemTotal`), Cancel (`closeSplitItemModal`) + "Tách món" (`executeSplitItem`). Note: this modal doubles as the transfer-target picker because `transferTargetTable` is set before opening it.

### D) Execute functions (all client-side mutations on `restaurantStore`, ~L5256-5540)
- `executeTransfer(sourceTable, targetTable)`: copies `sourceOrder.items` → target, clears source, flips table statuses (source→Available, target→Serving), recomputes `billAmount`, toasts, sets `selectedTableCode`.
- `executeMerge(sourceTable, targetTable)`: concatenates items into target, clears source.
- `executeSplitOrder(sourceTable, targetTable)`: divides `sourceOrder.items` into `splitOrderCount` chunks (Swal-asked), places chunk 2+ onto available tables found via `filteredTables`, keeps remainder on source.
- `executeSplitItem()`: clones selected items (with chosen qty, new id `${id}-split-${Date.now()}`) to target order, decrements/removes from source.
- `executeCancel()` (~L5535+): requires typing "HỦY" + manager PIN via Swal (`pin !== "1234"`), then calls Supabase RPC `hall_get_checkout_totals` + `hall_cancel_order_or_item` for real (non-mock) occupied tables.

> All of `executeTransfer/Merge/SplitOrder/SplitItem` mutate **local Pinia store state only** (`restaurantStore.tableOrders`, table `.status/.customerName/.billAmount`) — they do **not** persist to Supabase. Only `executeCancel` hits Supabase RPCs. This is a key gap if you're building a real `useTableOperations` composable.

